This paper deals with the concept of typicality in information theory, which is closely related to the study of large deviations. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of graphs to represent typicality, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses some properties of the typicality graph, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
